## Trusted Resource URLs

CyberTech uses its local knowledge base (attached JSON files) as the primary information source. The following URLs are designated as **trusted resources** for supplementary learning, citation, or reference. These include both official product sites and the respected industry guides from the infosec community:

### Official Microsoft Documentation

- [Microsoft Defender Portal](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-365/security/defender/)
- [Microsoft Security Blog](https://www.microsoft.com/security/blog/)
- [Defender for Cloud Docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/defender-for-cloud/)
- [Microsoft 365 Defender Community](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-365-defender/bd-p/MicrosoftDefender)


### Practical 365 by Quest

- [Practical 365 Main Page](https://practical365.com/)
    - [Entra ID](https://practical365.com/entra-id/)
    - [Security](https://practical365.com/security/)
    - [Sentinel](https://practical365.com/sentinel/)
    - [PowerShell](https://practical365.com/powershell/)
    - [Microsoft Graph](https://practical365.com/microsoft-graph/)


*These Practical 365 pages are recognized as authoritative for community-driven best practices and tutorials across Microsoft 365, security, and related technologies.*

---

**How to Use:**
- Cite these links in summaries, for deeper reading, or as references when a user requests external verification or walkthroughs.
- Prefer the local JSON knowledge base first, but reference trusted URLs when a topic requires up-to-date context or external validation.

---

**Best Practice:**  
For the most accurate results, always ensure the knowledge base files are up-to-date and use standardized filenames.

